  "description": "## üéØ Workflow Goal\n\nStill manually checking form responses in your inbox?\n\nWhat if every submission landed neatly in Airtable ‚Äî and you got a clean Slack message instantly?\n\nThat‚Äôs exactly what this workflow does.\n\nNo code, no delay ‚Äî just a smooth automation to keep your team in the loop:\n\n**Tally ‚Üí Airtable ‚Üí Slack**\n\nBuild an automated flow that:\n- receives Tally form submissions,\n- cleans up the data into usable fields,\n- stores the results in Airtable,\n- and automatically notifies a Slack channel.\n\n\n## Step 1 ‚Äì Connect Tally to n8n\n\n![automatiserformulairetallyetape1.png](fileId:1668)\n\n### What we‚Äôre setting up\n\nA Webhook node in POST mode.\n\n### Technical\n\n1. Add a Webhook node.  \n2. Set it to POST.  \n3. Copy the generated URL.  \n4. In Tally ‚Üí Integrations ‚Üí Webhooks ‚Üí paste this URL.  \n5. Submit a test response on your form to capture a sample structure.\n\n## Step 2 ‚Äì Clean the data\n\n![automatiserformulairetallyetape2.png](fileId:1670)\n\nAfter connecting Tally, you now receive raw data inside a fields[] array.\n\nLet‚Äôs convert that into something clean and structured.\n\n### Goal\n\nExtract key info like Full Name, Email, Phone, etc. into simple keys.\n\n### What we‚Äôre doing\n\nAdd a Set node to remap and clean the fields.\n\n### Technical\n\n1. Add a Set node right after the Webhook.  \n2. Add new values (String type) manually:\n   - Name: Full Name ‚Üí Value: {{$json[\"fields\"][0][\"value\"]}}  \n   - Name: Email ‚Üí Value: {{$json[\"fields\"][1][\"value\"]}}  \n   - Name: Phone ‚Üí Value: {{$json[\"fields\"][2][\"value\"]}}  \n   *(Adapt the indexes based on your form structure.)*\n\nUse the data preview in the Webhook node to check the correct order.\n\n**Output**\n\nYou now get clean data like:\n\n{ \"Full Name\": \"Jane Doe\",\n  \"Email\": \"jane@example.com\",\n  \"Phone\": \"+123456789\" }\n\n## Step 3 ‚Äì Send to Airtable\n\n![automatiserformulairetallyetape3.png](fileId:1667)\n\n‚úÖ Once the data is cleaned, let‚Äôs store it in Airtable automatically.\n\n**Goal**\n\nCreate one new Airtable row for each form submission.\n\nWhat we‚Äôre setting up\n\nAn Airtable ‚Äì Create Record node.\n\n**Technical**\n\n1. Add an Airtable node.  \n2. Authenticate or connect your API token.  \n3. Choose the base and table.  \n4. Map the fields:\n   - Name: {{$json[\"Full Name\"]}}  \n   - Email: {{$json[\"Email\"]}}  \n   - Phone: {{$json[\"Phone\"]}}\n\n**Output**\n\nEach submission creates a clean new row in your Airtable table.\n\n## Step 4 ‚Äì Add a delay\n\n![automatiserformulairetallyetape4.png](fileId:1669)\n\n‚åõ After saving to Airtable, it‚Äôs a good idea to insert a short pause ‚Äî this prevents actions like Slack messages from stacking too fast.\n\nGoal\n\nWait a few seconds before sending a Slack notification.\n\nWhat we‚Äôre setting up\n\nA Wait node for X seconds.\n\n‚úÖ Technical\n1. Add a Wait node.  \n2. Choose Wait for X minutes.  \n\n## Step 5 ‚Äì Send a message to Slack\n\n![automatiserformulairetallyetape5.png](fileId:1671)\n\nüí¨ Now that the record is stored, let‚Äôs send a Slack message to notify your team.\n\n**Goal**\nAutomatically alert your team in Slack when someone fills the form.\n\nWhat we‚Äôre setting up\n\nA Slack ‚Äì Send Message node.\n\n**Technical**\n\n1. Add a Slack node.  \n2. Connect your account.  \n3. Choose the target channel, like #leads.  \n4. Use this message format:\n\n**New lead received!**\n\nName: {{$json[\"Full Name\"]}}  \n\nEmail: {{$json[\"Email\"]}}  \n\nPhone: {{$json[\"Phone\"]}}  \n\n\nOutput\n\nYour Slack team is notified instantly, with all lead info in one clean message.\n\nWorkflow Complete\n\nYour automation now looks like this:  \n\n**Tally ‚Üí Clean ‚Üí Airtable ‚Üí Wait ‚Üí Slack**\n\nEvery submission turns into clean data, gets saved in Airtable, and alerts your team on Slack ‚Äî fully automated, no extra work.",
